e>The Badass Barbarian Shaman</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(12/11/01 1:02:25 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.alexander.darkwave.org.uk/xora.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: rogue race</span><hr size=1> Stats wise, halflings make the best rogues. At least, that's what I thought. There's a lot of debate about the relevance of stats for a rogue.<br>
<br>
Halflings have the highest natural DEX and AGI. Two stats that are the basis for a rogue. They also have a higher than average base STA. Items with +STR are very common so you shouldn't really waste time putting points into that. My shaman has a STR around 150 and that's without even trying as WIS is my primary stat.<br>
<br>
However, I spoke to a high level rogue the other night that said high DEX on a rogue was a bad thing as you proc too much and build up too much aggro. But I figured this was the problem of the group taunter, not the rogue. A rogue is there for damage output, saying that a rogue should damage less is just a waste of the class.<br>
<br>
IMO aggro is the problem of the taunter, not the rogue. Being a shaman, I know all about aggro, cast slow at the start of the fight and, 8 times out of 10, the mob will come straight for you. If your taunter can't keep ahead of the aggro curve, get a better taunter 8) <p><DIV align=center>
